'Cause vampire or not,
the last thing I want to see

35:40.405 --> 35:41.840
is your lost boy.

35:41.840 --> 35:43.742
Damn, Peez, you gotta
stop lurking.

35:45.844 --> 35:47.812
It's time for a strategy sesh.

35:47.812 --> 35:49.881
Nah, I listened
to you all day,

35:49.881 --> 35:51.282
and the only thing
your little tricks did

35:51.282 --> 35:52.717
was make the wrong girl
look my way.

35:52.717 --> 35:53.952
I'm out.

35:53.952 --> 35:58.890
This is a long con,
Milton. Trust me.

35:58.890 --> 36:02.327
Lizzie's nemesis Dana
liking you, oh,

36:02.327 --> 36:06.698
that's the puzzle piece you need
to crack Lizzie's candy shell

36:06.698 --> 36:08.633
and get to her gooey center.

36:08.633 --> 36:12.337
Today was a total win
for you.

36:12.337 --> 36:15.740
You hate Lizzie.
Why do you care?

36:20.645 --> 36:23.648
Some people just want
to watch the world burn.

36:39.664 --> 36:40.865
You mad at me

36:40.865 --> 36:43.334
'cause we lost the game?
No.

36:43.334 --> 36:46.037
I'm mad at the world, and you
just happen to be in it.

36:49.374 --> 36:52.277
Well, you're about to be.

36:53.545 --> 36:55.980
I did a little spell
at the game.

36:55.980 --> 36:59.384
I made Kaleb drop the ball.

36:59.384 --> 37:04.656
And I totally did
black magic with Hope.

37:04.656 --> 37:07.592
Well, let's just
call this what it is.

37:09.060 --> 37:10.728
You betrayed me.

37:12.764 --> 37:15.600
I was worried about
disappointing Dad.

37:17.702 --> 37:20.305
So I disappointed
you instead.

37:33.118 --> 37:35.420
I'll forgive you

37:35.420 --> 37:39.057
if you promise
not to keep secrets about

37:39.057 --> 37:41.526
doing black magic
with Hope.

37:41.526 --> 37:42.994
You're my sister,

37:42.994 --> 37:45.096
my best friend,

37:45.096 --> 37:46.598
and she spent the last ten years

37:46.598 --> 37:48.733
making us feel like
we don't matter.

37:48.733 --> 37:50.869
And I don't like
feeling that way.

37:50.869 --> 37:54.506
Not from Hope, and not
from girls like Dana,

37:54.506 --> 37:55.774
not from Dad

37:55.774 --> 37:57.976
and not from you.

37:57.976 --> 38:01.012
I promise.

38:01.012 --> 38:02.580
Okay? I'm sorry.

38:02.580 --> 38:04.516
It's okay.

38:05.817 --> 38:09.154
I mean, betrayal
and all aside,

38:09.154 --> 38:11.089
you had my back today.

38:11.089 --> 38:12.991
And you had mine.

38:20.765 --> 38:24.502
So, what are we
gonna do about Dad?

38:26.437 --> 38:30.074
More like what is he
gonna do to us?

38:35.613 --> 38:38.483
♪ ♪

38:46.691 --> 38:48.092
Where are they?

38:48.092 --> 38:49.961
Gone.

38:49.961 --> 38:53.398
I found this on the windshield
when I got back.

38:58.036 --> 39:01.039
LANDON:
Dear Hope, you strike me
as the kind of person

39:01.039 --> 39:02.941
who's not so big
on second chances,

39:02.941 --> 39:06.644
much less third,
but I'm gonna give it a shot.

39:06.644 --> 39:10.048
♪ How long can you wait? ♪

39:10.048 --> 39:12.116
I can't explain why
I took that knife.

39:12.116 --> 39:13.918
Believe me, I wish I could.

39:13.918 --> 39:17.021
But maybe I can explain
why I ran.

39:17.021 --> 39:19.591
I have never been welcomed
anywhere in my life.

39:19.591 --> 39:21.025
I'm always the extra.

39:21.025 --> 39:23.595
The mouth they didn't want
to feed.

39:23.595 --> 39:25.797
If I caused trouble, I was out.

39:25.797 --> 39:27.165
When you grow up like that,

39:27.165 --> 39:29.167
you learn how
to protect yourself.

39:29.167 --> 39:32.270
You do what you have to do
to survive.

39:32.270 --> 39:34.138
I never had a real family.

39:34.138 --> 39:35.807
And that's not meant to
make you feel sorry for me.

39:35.807 --> 39:38.109
I'm trying to
make you understand.

39:38.109 --> 39:40.879
I lied to protect myself,

39:40.879 --> 39:43.648
but in doing so,
I hurt you.

39:43.648 --> 39:46.584
And for that,
I will be forever sorry.

39:46.584 --> 39:48.620
♪ Rise on up... ♪

39:48.620 --> 39:49.954
Dad...

39:51.589 --> 39:53.524
I can explain.

39:53.524 --> 39:58.529
♪ Don't need eyes to see ♪

40:00.765 --> 40:03.768
♪ It ain't over, love ♪

40:03.768 --> 40:06.638
♪ This I swear ♪

40:06.638 --> 40:09.607
♪ We're coming up... ♪

40:09.607 --> 40:12.110
LANDON:
The time I spent with you
the other night

40:12.110 --> 40:14.312
was one of the happiest
moments in my life.

40:14.312 --> 40:16.881
I hate that I ruined it.

40:16.881 --> 40:19.117
Your school's secret is
safe with me.

40:19.117 --> 40:21.786
With regret, Landon.

40:26.824 --> 40:29.694
♪ ♪

40:39.704 --> 40:41.973
DORIAN: Trying to
make a run for it?

40:41.973 --> 40:44.942
Yeah.

40:44.942 --> 40:47.979
I just noticed this gate
wasn't locking the other day.

40:47.979 --> 40:49.981
You worried about
people getting out?

40:49.981 --> 40:52.550
I'm worried about
what might want to get in.

40:54.152 --> 40:57.855
We've gotten cozy here.

40:57.855 --> 40:59.157
Careless.

41:00.958 --> 41:05.363
I'd forgotten the world is full
of nasty surprises.

41:05.363 --> 41:07.632
I don't know what the story is
behind that knife,

41:07.632 --> 41:10.635
but whatever it is, I...

41:12.036 --> 41:13.705
...saw something today
I never thought

41:13.705 --> 41:16.240
I'd ever see in this lifetime.

41:16.240 --> 41:17.775
And it scared me.

41:19.377 --> 41:21.779
You know, I opened this school
to protect these kids.

41:24.015 --> 41:27.285
To protect my daughters.

41:31.255 --> 41:32.857
How am I supposed to
protect them

41:32.857 --> 41:38.029
from stuff that's
not supposed to exist?
